Auto managed configurations can now declare a "public static ManagedConfig mc;" in an APSConfig subclass and call isManaged() and waitUntilManaged() on it to ensure it has been populated with config values before using it.
- Added admin and service authentication to aps-rpc-http-transport. - Changed getObject(name) to retrieveObject(name) in APSSession.
Now also updated lastUsed timestamp on saveObject() and retrieveObject().

- Restructured project structure. - Removed category APS-Enterprise. - Added category APS-Auth and APS-Data. - APSSimpleUserService moved to APS-Auth. - APSDataSource and APSOpenJPAProvider moved to APS-Data. - No longer any subcategory APIs. All APIs reside in APS-APIs.
Manually fixed some refactorings that IntelliJ missed in XML files.
Added sub roles to roles in APSSimpleUserService.
Updated APSUserAdminWeb to support subroles for roles.
Divided roles into master roles and sub roles in menu tree.
Added control that users can only have master roles.
APSUserAdminWeb cosmetica + small bug fixes in APSSimpleUserServiceProvider.
Now automatically creates "apsadmin" user and "apsadmin" role if they don't exists.
Removed non working profile to update version.
~/.aps/apsfs is now the default root for APSFilesystemService if aps.filesystem.root system property is not set.

Moved connect() and disconnect() code from activator to service provider with delayed connect until first service call due to that connect does things that cannot be done at activation. The previous code created a server startup deadlock situation where in activation we were waiting for something that would not happen until activation was done. The server deploys bundles sequentially without activation timeout ...
Updated APSDiscoveryService to use APSGroups instead. This made it 90% smaller.
Modified APSDiscoveryServiceProvider to make use of APSGroups for discovery.
aps-34 APS-APIs split refactoring: Cancelled! This was a bad idea. This commit represents what needed to be restored after a revert.

aps-35 Also implement org.osgi.service.jpa.EntityManagerFactoryBuilder: This version now implements org.osgi.jpa.EntityManagerFactoryBuilder, but it cannot be registered as a service with this API since at least Virgo then complains that it has a different version of this interface and refuses to deploy bundle.
Updated aps-openjpa-provider to import javax.persistence.* rather than export it. This API must be provided by the server or by other api bundle.
Moved out the extender code from APSConfigServiceActivator into separate APSConfigServiceExtender that now receives the bundle events.
Added info logging also for managed config setup.
Changed background color for code boxes in javadoc.
APSSimpleUserServiceAdmin now deals with UserAdmin and RoleAdmin subclasses rather than User and Role.
Should now handle "><!--APSVER>1.0.0<" strings so that it matches both version tags and property tags.

Started using tiles-maven-plugin and breaking out things like documentation generation and deploying to server into tiles. Since I previously used the maven-antrun-plugin to deploy to the server and ant of course failed (when doesn't it ?) when called from a tile I had to make a new ServerDeployPlugin to copy jars and wars to the server pickup directory.
APSNoServiceAvailableException has now moved to APSToolsLib.
APSNoServiceAvailableException has now moved to APSToolsLib.
APSNoServiceAvailableException has now moved to APSToolsLib.
Added a new createSession() variant to support distributed sessions. If that is a good or bad idea is another issue ...
Now uses more settings.xml properties for deployment paths.
Added a new createSession() variant to support distributed sessions. If that is a good or bad idea is another issue ...
Added import package since one exception has moved to another bundle and package.

Now double stores callable methods as "method" name only and "method(type,...,type)". It is now the latter that is returned by getMethodNames(), while getMethodCallable(method) first looks in the longer map and if not found there looks in the name only map.
Added defaults for production environment in RPCServletConfig.
- Renamed APSAuthenticationService to APSAuthService. - Now throws new APSAuthMethodNotSupportedException. - Renamed CredentialType to AuthMethod.
Updated the APSAuthService to also handle a role being required.
Javadoc change to be compatible with JavadocParser of MarkdownDoc.
Updated due to changes in APSAuthService API.
Updated RPCServlet due to changes in APSAdminWebLoginHandler.
Forgot to change artifact name before building, deploying, and generating documentation which resulted in wrong name for the docs and depoyment even though cosmetics.
Oops! Registered the service with a wrong name!
Updated TabPanel.refreshTabs() to do a more clean refresh.
Documentation generated by last deploy run.

- Updated the RPC protocols (forgot to do the reality test! It is impossible to resolve named parameters). - StreamedRPCProtocol now have 2 variants of parseRequest(...) one taking an InputStream and one taking a parameter Map. The latter for HTTP transports. - Added StreamedHTTPProtocol. This extends StreamedRPCProtocol and implies that any returned RPCError is actually an HTTPError subclass providing an http status code. This for a bit better interaction between HTTP transports and protocols wanting to support HTTP status codes rather than writing their own response. A REST type protocol is still not fully possible since we are still calling OSGi services by service class and method. - APSExternalProtocolHTTPTransportProvider now supports ?params=value for GET. - new JSONHTTP protocol tries to be as HTTP friendly as possible talking JSON and for GET can handle parameters with "?params=param:...:param" but only with primitives and String parameters. For POST and PUT a JSON array of objects or primitives can be sent as parameters.
Added System.out.println(...) and e.printStackTrace() if no logger has been provided for when onService* throws exceptions.

Dumb bug that was damn difficult to find have now been fixed. I apparently got interrupted while implementing setDataTypeClass(...) and never finished implementing it resulting in getDataTypeClass() returning null and causing an NPE (this should never be null!).
The APSExternalProtocolExtender now also provides special information about services that can potentially be called as REST having methods starting with post, put, get or delete.
Added REST support by a new JSONREST protocol and support for REST in both APSExternalProtocolService and the APSExternalProtocolHTTPTransportProvider.
Generated license header info for new JSONREST class.
Generated license header info for new JSONREST class.

Put documentation generation in a profile to avoid having all documentation always regenerated on each build.
Reverted putting doc generation in a profile since active profiles are not forwarded to tiles.
